# CODEOWNERS — SportMind Telegram AI Bot Starter Kit
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file defines who is automatically requested to review pull requests
# based on which files are changed. GitHub enforces these rules: a PR cannot
# be merged until the required reviewers have approved it.
#
# Review rights are held by the community, not the project founder.
# See GOVERNANCE.md for how Trusted Reviewers are appointed.
#
# Format: <path pattern>  <@reviewer> [<@reviewer> ...]
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── DEFAULT ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All files not matched by a more specific rule require review from the
# global Trusted Reviewer team. This team is maintained in GitHub and
# populated as Founding Calibrators are confirmed.
#
# Until the first Trusted Reviewers are appointed, this file is a declaration
# of intent. The first PRs will be reviewed by whoever is nominated first.
#
# Replace the placeholder team below with your GitHub org team once created:
# * @SportMind/trusted-reviewers

* @SportMind/trusted-reviewers


# ── PROMPTS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Prompt changes have the highest impact — they define agent intelligence.
# Require 2 reviewers. Prefer reviewers who hold calibration records in the
# relevant sport or domain (enforced by convention, not tooling).
#
# Note: GitHub CODEOWNERS does not enforce a minimum reviewer count here —
# that is set in branch protection rules (Settings → Branches → main →
# Require N approvals). Set this to 2 for the prompts/ directory.

prompts/                        @SportMind/trusted-reviewers


# ── CONFIGS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Config changes affect deployed bot behaviour. Require Trusted Reviewer sign-off.

config/                         @SportMind/trusted-reviewers


# ── EXAMPLES ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Examples are the primary onboarding surface. Accuracy matters.

examples/                       @SportMind/trusted-reviewers


# ── GOVERNANCE AND OWNERSHIP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Changes to GOVERNANCE.md, CODEOWNERS, and LICENSE require Maintainer-level
# approval (3 approvals, as specified in GOVERNANCE.md).
# The Maintainers team is a subset of Trusted Reviewers.

GOVERNANCE.md                   @SportMind/maintainers
.github/CODEOWNERS              @SportMind/maintainers
LICENSE                         @SportMind/maintainers


# ── CONTRIBUTING AND README ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Documentation changes that affect contributor onboarding or public-facing
# description of the kit. One Trusted Reviewer approval sufficient.

CONTRIBUTING.md                 @SportMind/trusted-reviewers
README.md                       @SportMind/trusted-reviewers


# ── CHANGELOG ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Changelog is updated as part of every release PR. Any Trusted Reviewer can approve.

CHANGELOG.md                    @SportMind/trusted-reviewers


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SETUP CHECKLIST (for repository administrators)
#
# 1. Create two GitHub teams in your org:
#    - @SportMind/trusted-reviewers  (Trusted Reviewers + Maintainers)
#    - @SportMind/maintainers        (Maintainers only — subset of above)
#
# 2. Enable branch protection on `main`:
#    Settings → Branches → Add rule → Branch name: main
#    ✓ Require a pull request before merging
#    ✓ Require approvals: 2 (for prompts/ and configs/), 1 (for docs)
#    ✓ Require review from Code Owners
#    ✓ Dismiss stale pull request approvals when new commits are pushed
#    ✓ Restrict who can push to matching branches → @SportMind/maintainers
#
# 3. Add first Trusted Reviewers to @SportMind/trusted-reviewers as
#    Founding Calibrators are confirmed in SportMind/SportMind.
#
# 4. Remove this checklist comment once setup is complete.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
